commit.message: Deleting unnecessary files attached to the repository.
Changed the logic and took out the LED indicators

This is an updated code with all four cases being covered for data to the app and directly with the uC. They now work in sync, except for the disabling of the seats on the physical app. I have not figured out how to write data back to the BLE module. It will not be done by the late demo either.I am debating whether or not to pull out the LEDs right now, but they will be pulled and pins will open up on the uC.
Working bluetooth and app with overlay for calling when seatbelt hasn't been detected on seats (with no disabling on that respective seat) for ~10 seconds

Had an issue with building the app. Fixed it by creating a new project. Also, I got the bluetooth module to connect to the app and it is parsing data in realtime. It has the core component completed and just needs a few extra things to complete the project.

I believe I actually, finally, got the bluetooth to work. I need to test out using original hardware - IR sensors. Device does recognize bluetooth state and outputs it in console or message on device if off or unsupported.
Adding this as I now have a time delay at the beginning of the app.
All seats (except drivers: on purpose) can be disabled/enabled, with a photoshopped picture difference
Redoing the swift code for the app. Still trying to learn how to operate it. The layout is done for the app loading screen and the base model
Added a bluetooth module and got it to work with a terminal app on a Windows computer. Correct data is being passed and updated in realtime.
